AGI -&nbsp;"Today is a date that deeply marked the memory and conscience of our nation. It was on May 9, 1978 when Aldo Moro's body, barbaricly murdered by the Red Brigades, was found in the trunk of a car in Via Caetani in Rome. The same day he fell, by mafia hand, Peppino Impastato. And it was on May 9, 2021 the day when the beatification of Rosario Livatino was proclaimed, magistrate killed by Stidda. A state man, a brave activist and a Judge, whose sacrifices must not be forgotten and should not be vain. Not by chance in 2007 the Italian Parliament established on 9 May the 'Day of Memory' &nbsp;dedicated to the memory of all the victims of terrorism and the massacres of this matrix. Let us not forget them and treasure their teachings." He writes on social media the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, who adds: "We owe it to all innocent victims, to those who sacrificed their lives for our freedom. We owe it to ourselves, to our history, to our homeland and to our children, to whom there was before us and to whom there will be after us. We owe it to Italy and to the values we love," he concludes.&nbsp;
