&nbsp;AGI - "I don't think the disciplinary proceedings against Serena Bortone do justice to the affair, or do well to the Rai." The president of the Rai, Marinella Soldi, said this about the Scurati affair of which yesterday spoke the ad of the company of Viale Mazzini Roberto Sergio, during the hearing in the Supervisory Commission.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"As reported by the ad in the Commission - it has specified President Rai - partly tells what happened, not citing important aspects. Without prejudice to corporate policy, the so-called Scurati case is still subject to verification by the Corporate Internal Audit Manager, for which the President has delegates. The results in the draft of this audit have been viewed both by me and by the ad and show a much more complex situation than that described by the AD, which requires a more complete approach."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, in a joint note, the Equal Opportunities Commissions of Fnsi, Usigrai and Odg and the Giulia Journalists have manifested "full solidarity and closeness to the journalist Serena&nbsp;Bortone&nbsp; object of contestation of the leadership of the Rai who opened a disciplinary procedure for having violated the policy" on social communication: in the substance, for having warned Sara audience".
&nbsp;
For the Equal Opportunities Commissions of Fnsi, Usigrai and Odg and the Giulia Journalist Association "is a ridiculous accusation in the digital age, which fails to cover the misdemeanour attempt to sanction the host to have squared the veil of censuresus, so far denied how clearly evident. She is charged with the damage of image of the Rai, due to the case from the planetary echo, instead of those who tried to prevent Scurati from his monologue".
&nbsp;
From here "the strong concern for the use of disciplinary instruments with intimidating vetero taste with the intent to reduce to silence critical voices, forgetting that criticism is the basis of democracy. That is why we will continue to watch," he concluded.&nbsp;
