In Transatlantic in the morning there were already possible 'variable geometry'. Who, between leghisti and FI, hypothesized a Rixi race at the Palace of navigation. Those who gave for certain the candidacy of Rosso, Ligurian coordinator of Brothers of Italy, a party that has long sought to lead a Northern Region. The first hypothesis - that is the possibility for the League to lead the Liguria - would then compensate the party of Matteo Salvini of the possible 'loss' &nbsp; of the Venetian fief, where Luca Zaia can not relapse in 2025, obliged to a stop after the second term. Although - he observes a source of FdI - "the League at this moment is weak in Liguria". However, neither Rixi nor Rosso would be available to the state for an application that the investigation would make uphill.
&nbsp;
But it is also necessary to see if the other road will be accessible, that is, that of prolonged regency of Piana, until the expiration of the legislature, also considering the fact that the name of the latter has appeared recently (but it is not investigated) in an investigation of the Procura of Genoa on vip festini with drugs and escort, stamped as "fake news" from the interested party.
<h2> The Pd-M5s-Avs axis calls for a step back</h2>
On the front of the oppositions, from the axis Pd-M5s-Avs comes the strong demand for resignation of President Toti. "The combination of politics and private enterprises with milionary interests linked to public administration is a real disease to be eradicated. And it is the main reason why I believe that Toti must resign and that the word should be returned to the citizens of Liguria", says Nicola Fratoianni>, secretary of Italian Left. "It is necessary to go quickly to new elections. Only new elections can bring political clarity to a region that is now a concentrate of interests, that is, companies, companies and people who have financed the election campaign of President Toti, and who are then the same companies that have obtained permissions or delibere from the same Region", says Angelo Bonelli> of Green and Left Allenza. "Elections immediately" is also the line of the Democratic Party.
&nbsp;
The leaders of Liguria, in a note, break the Hindus and ask that immediately begin that process of regeneration of the regional institutions of which the former Minister Andrea Orlando speaks. "It must close the season of the center of Liguria. Toti dimetta and there are immediately new elections", we read in the text signed by the leaders Pd of Genoa and Liguria. A request that goes beyond the judicial record. It moves, rather, from negative judgment on the regional government: "In these years the Democratic Party at all levels has denounced the damage and consequences that this policy management has caused to health, work, infrastructure, social services." This, along with the "just distance from the electoral deadlines, calls for civic mobilization: in the name of the morality of politics and a different idea of Liguria". A position that follows Orlando's. The exponent dem is among the first to urge, in the face of a "desolant square", a process of regeneration that cannot begin if not with the resignation of the governor: "It must be avoided that this very serious short circuit prejudges the interests of the region and the big investments that concern it. It is therefore necessary to prevent the situation from falling. There is a need to start a strong process of regeneration in the interest of the region and Ligurians."
