AGI -&nbsp;Fare da argine, "with its own bodies and voices" to the reform of the premiership. Elly Schlein is present at the Democratic Party's senators' meeting on the day when the debate on institutional reforms begins in the Senate House > and takes the opportunity to launch the national demonstration on 2 June >, the feast of the Republic. The mobilization, it is learned, will be held in Rome, probably in Piazza del Popolo, already the theater of the mobilization of the Pd on 11 November. On that occasion the dems brought about 50 thousand people to the square and the hope is, at least, to equal the result.
&nbsp;
"I ask you to mobilize us strongly: on two June we will make a demonstration on the Constitution and federal Europe against the pre-emptive > and differentiated autonomy," says Schlein to the dem senators. The message, however, is addressed to the whole community of the Pd and beyond. It is clear, the secretary explains, that the right is accelerating to be able to put on the plate of the electoral campaign the reform of the premier. So this is the reasoning, we must raise the battle for the constitution outside Parliament. Behind the secretary, in the Senate Defense Commission room, there is a quote from Sandro Pertini.
&nbsp;
To read it to senators is the group leader Francesco Boccia: "Behind every article in the Constitution there are hundreds of young people dead in the Resistance and that is why we have to defend it, costs what it costs." Following the words of the Partisan President, Schlein launches his appeal: "We use our bodies and our voices to make wall compared to this attempt. They try to advance on the dangerous terrain of the premiership and differentiated autonomy to have something to flag in the election campaign. It is dangerous because we are talking about the constitutional rules that hold up democracy." Bringing this mobilization into the country, on the other hand, appears to the dems as one of the last arrows left at the arch.
&nbsp;
"We of the PD in commission have put it all to open a real confrontation," says the group leader in the Constitutional Affairs Commission, Andrea Giorgis. >
&nbsp;
"In the face of this attitude we found silence or arrogance of those who say that it is following the electoral campaign commitments. As if the constitution can be the subject of electoral campaign. Even when we realized that our arguments made a breach, we witnessed an embarrassed silence," adds Senator dem. The group leader Francesco Boccia also dwells on the silence of the majority: "Anziché&nbsp; participate in propaganda conferences like that of today at the House", says Boccia, "the majority of Giorgia Meloni would better confront Parliament where, instead, only 9 senators are enrolled in general discussion. The truth is one: we risk saying goodbye to our parliamentary republic to put all power in the hands of Giorgia."
&nbsp;
To contest the choice of the Pd to bring the mobilization in the square on June 2 is the president of the senators of Forza Italia, Maurizio Gasparri: "Schlein and comrades do not respect the Feast of the Republic of June 2 and want, on that date, to make a further demonstration against the reforms under discussion in Parliament to modernize the Republic. They trample the dates with an institutional teppism worthy of best cause."
&nbsp;
To answer is still Boccia: "I tell Gasparri that we are certainly not the institutional thugs but rather those who have not written our Constitution think today to overturn it. We will manifest on June 2, with great respect for the initiatives and the Festival that will take place that day, precisely to remember the roots of our Constitution that reminds us that our is a parliamentary Republic".
&nbsp;

